<p>Make sure you have give:
    * Atleast 50G to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/</code>
    * Atleast 2G to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">boot</code>
    * Atleast 20G to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">swap</code></p>
<h2 id="cuda">CUDA</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Follow <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">.deb</code> file procedure for installation on CUDA website. The <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">runfile</code> option doesnâ€™t work well.</li>
  <li></li>
</ol>

<h2 id="tex-live">TeX Live</h2>
<ol>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sudo apt-get install texlive</code></li>
  <li>If for some reason you cannot install packages with <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">tlmgr</code>, use:
    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>sudo tlmgr option repository ftp://tug.org/historic/systems/texlive/2017/tlnet-final
</code></pre></div>    </div>
    <p>to go back to add an old repository.</p>
  </li>
  <li>Make sure you check the HEAD package on CTAN, in case a package installation fails.</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="python-with-anaconda3">Python with Anaconda3</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Install Python with <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">anaconda</code> using the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sh</code> file by running:
    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>chmod +x
./Anaconda3-&lt;version&gt;.sh
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>If for some reason you need to install again, delete <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">~/.conda/</code> before setting a new environment.</li>
</ol>

